 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoyoteblack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteblack</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 1/18/01 11:10:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uinkelongdirk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Inke Longdirk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/01 2:07:53 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/inke28/murray.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue against other classes, PvP servers...</span><hr size=1> &quot;A rogue at 25ish, shouldn't win a 1 one 1 duel against any class. If they do win, then the person that lost needs to quit.&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
Yeah, this is total bullshite. I know many OBR who have beaten every class at times, at all levels. I'm sure the Shanks have too, as well as most other PvP rogues. Granted the finger wigglers can be very tough at low 20's. They are by no means impossible to beat, even when skilled.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/01 3:07:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue against other classes, PvP servers...</span><hr size=1> On a PvP server, AC is just part of your resistances.  It is Melee resist.  You need Magic, Fire, Cold, Diesease, and Poison resists as much as you need Melee resist.<br>
<br>
With your resistances up, Pumice ready, and hopefully a body of water near, you should be able to hammer a caster of your same level.  The lower your resists, the more damgae you will take, the more your movement will be restricted, the faster you will die.<br>
<br>
Casters have an advantage. Thier classes take less skill to master.  That does not make them undefeatable. <p>Majestyk, <a href="http://Server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a>, <a href="http://www.talonguard.org/shanks">Shanks</a>, <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5034">Vallon Zek!</a>

We as Shanks, have chosen the hard path. In the hardness of it, is where we find the glory.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=pageboy>Pageboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/01 3:52:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ROFL</span><hr size=1> I hope i can meet that guy that cut down rogues. I have taken on two necros at the same time, killed one, ran off, bandaged to half, came back and killed the other one. The key is being ready. I always carry around cure disease and poison potions and pumice or the rod from CT if i can score one.<br>
<br>
Rogues are great for 1 on 1. One class i worry about are SK's. They are super mean if they get a darkness on you and with the new HT changes they can take almost all my hp's. I dont worry about getting rooted too much with a MR of 98, 'cept if the person is 8 levels above me. Resists just dont mean nothing then.<br>
<br>
Another class i dont like are Druids with their damage shields. i pretty much take as much damage as i give, not cool at all. No use pumicing because the mana cost and cast time on their shields is so low not worth the pumice.<br>
