k thanks for flames<br>
Bomban <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiamwotan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>I am Wotan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/yinyang.gif border=0 BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/01 8:33:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/mask2a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue against other classes, PvP servers...</span><hr size=1> Duels are for blue servers.  On PvP the fight is rarely between two equal levels, and almost never at equal levels of preparedness.  For a meaningful prediction of outcome class, level, equipment, circumstances, and the person behind the screen all have to be taken into account, in no particular order (except level first).  <br>
<br>
While I'd agree with most of what Bomban said in theory (assuming he meant even-cons) lets just shift the discussion a little.  Lets say the rogue is lvl 27, equipped with SBD, high resists, low delay weapons, a nice bow and plenty of arrows, sow potions, snare poison and pumice. Lets also say the fight takes place in an enclosed area like the Qeynos arena.  Starting to get the picture?  You don't even have to be twinked, if you spend your time working on equipment rather than leveling, you can get pretty tough for your level.  <br>
<br>
As a caster, if you cant get the movement advantage or invulnerability you are going to have some trouble getting yer spell off.  If you don't have the right ones memmed then Marr help ya.  Not sure when necros get an invulnerability spell, wizards can use shadowstep to advantage etc.  A pet is going to give a rogue fits, but if that SBD goes off ...<br>
<br>
