<font size=2><b><i>It is better to have less thunder in the mouth and more lightning in the hand.  - Apache Proverb</font></font></font></i></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.13thshadowcompany.com/svimages/new_post.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/01 12:21:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue against other classes, PvP servers...</span><hr size=1> He who is most prepared will win. Fair fight? What fair fight? I have only had maybe two fair fights in my career. And that's fine I suppose. I'd expect nothing less. Why pick a fight with someone better then you?<br>
<br>
And please, don't throw out the necro crock. Necro's owning people have extremely little to do with skills, they are simply overpowered. I was reading through Vaslin's eqcaster one time on the necro section and honestly, ever few seconds I was like "Dang, I didn't know they could do that!" So don't think you'r all big and bad just because you play an overpowered class.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><center><a href="http://silentdecree.guildhappy.com"><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/MatrixSig26.gif"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/01 11:51:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue against other classes, PvP servers...</span><hr size=1> Hmmm, seems the only classes I have trouble taking down within a few levels of me are PREPARED druids, Shaman and SKs Wizzies, and Necros.<br>
<br>
If a druid has his damage shield and SoW burried under a bunch of buffs, its almost a losing battle (Well, if you have sow potions, Jboots, or snare poison, SoW isn't too big a deal), but that damage shield hurts.  Otherwise, he has no chance to kill me, and if I have snare or SBD procs, he's done for.<br>
<br>
Shaman are a little tougher too.  They have decent AC (making spells harder to interrupt), and Spirit of Cheatah *grumbles at Wotan* and gate to get away.<br>
<br>
SKs- High AC, High damage weapons, Darkness, Shadowstep.  These guys are tough to chop down if you don't have good MR and aren't good at avoiding their weapon swings.  Also, I generally bail after I get HTed, hehe.<br>
<br>
Necros- They usually aren't a worry to me anymore, unless they get the jump on me and root/snare me.  Pet can be annoying if you're going for the kill.  They usually will just Shadowstep and gate on me though. *grumbles about shadowstep being unbalancing in PvP*<br>
<br>
Wizzards- If they manage to root you, you're pretty much done unless you have great Fire and cold resists.  A couple good shots from these guys hurts.  Though, like other pure casters, will go down quick if you can stay on them.  Shadowstep sucks though when you're going for the kill.<br>
<br>
I've attacked and killed plenty of red/yellow cons in my day.  Its all about getting the jump and being properly equipped and prepared though. <p><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</b><BR>
Crime Boss of Vallon Zek<BR>
{Order of the Black Rose}<BR>
---------------------------<BR><i>
"No man can separate what we create...<BR> Unstoppable, untouchable, OBR at its finest.  <BR>Thugs for life, assassins for hire.  Can ya feel me?  Well feel this..."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/01 12:21:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue against other classes, PvP servers...</span><hr size=1> Bomban, I'm assuming that english isn't your first language.<br>
<br>
I'm on Vallon.  Are you?  If so, is Bamban your charachter name? <p>Majestyk, <a href="http://Server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a>, <a href="http://www.talonguard.org/shanks">Shanks</a>, <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5034">Vallon Zek!</a>

We as Shanks, have chosen the hard path. In the hardness of it, is where we find the glory.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushariin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shariin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/01 12:33:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue against other classes, PvP servers...</span><hr size=1> A rogue can take out a shaman, Karlek - granted it's not easy, but it can be done (I beat one 5 levels above me last weekend).  Now, I play on a blue server, but I'm not picky about making people debuff before a duel.  I find them, I fight them, may the best duelist win.  Admittedly, I tend to lose against buffed, petted, fm mages about my level, but that's a weakness I intend to work on. ;)<br>
<br>
Be prepared.  As Majestyk said, AC is just another resist - I'd balance towards AC and MR as &quot;default&quot; resists as MR covers all the root/darkness spells and mobility is king.  Get a golem wand if you can (you're a mite low to pick one up yourself, admittedly), or a pumice if you can't.  Carry potions - SoW, cures, damage shield.<br>
<br>
From my personal experience, though...<br>
Clerics are popcorn.  Bards are basically impossible unless they handicap themselves.  Petted mages are tough (or maybe it's just that all the ones I've fought have JBoots and I don't?).  Necros aren't too bad, but they can kill you after you kill them.  Shamen are an interesting mix (nice buffs, decent AC) and have some nice pvp abilities but I don't lose to them too often.  Wizzes are easy.  Ranger have nasty DS and SoW, but take care of that and it's not too bad.  Warriors are easy unless they're smart *and* skilled - a high delay weapon and jousting can be quite annoying.  Druids always try to kite - dispell their SoW and they're SOL.  Enchanters can be tough unless you get the jump on them - they basically need to Tash to get things to stick.  Pallies are like warriors, except with more hits.  Haven't fought a similarly levelled SK yet. <p><style type="text/css">
